1
00:00:03,900 --> 00:00:09,203
There is nothing that is not Kṛṣṇa
and personal.

2
00:00:09,279 --> 00:00:14,235
Sometimes people misunderstand
that Brahman and Brahmajyoti,

3
00:00:14,235 --> 00:00:17,925
it only appears to be impersonal
from a distance.

4
00:00:18,193 --> 00:00:22,042
[Everything is Personal]

5
00:00:22,129 --> 00:00:27,738
As you look
with greater scrutiny and close-up,

6
00:00:27,738 --> 00:00:30,972
then you see
that everything is personal.

7
00:00:31,219 --> 00:00:32,530
Sometimes when Guru Mahārāj

8
00:00:32,530 --> 00:00:35,695
would push this to 
an extreme degree,

9
00:00:35,819 --> 00:00:39,528
Jajavar Mahārāj would become
a little flustered, he’d be like,

10
00:00:39,528 --> 00:00:42,672
“You mean this table
is a person?”

11
00:00:42,764 --> 00:00:45,273
Guru Mahārāj: “Yes.”

12
00:00:47,502 --> 00:00:53,007
Because he’s saying,
if an object

13
00:00:53,007 --> 00:00:57,388
is a cluster of subjective concepts
floating in consciousness,

14
00:00:57,388 --> 00:01:01,234
then ultimately this is floating
in consciousness, and consciousness

15
00:01:01,234 --> 00:01:05,207
can never ultimately
be divorced of personality.

16
00:01:05,207 --> 00:01:12,365
That’s why ṛṣis address
the inanimate in personal ways—

17
00:01:13,284 --> 00:01:16,459
what appears to be inanimate.

18
00:01:17,321 --> 00:01:21,168
So the ocean; the river; Jamuna.

19
00:01:23,292 --> 00:01:28,255
Jala brahma: spiritual water.

20
00:01:28,255 --> 00:01:33,143
Dāru brahma: spiritual wood.

21
00:01:34,190 --> 00:01:39,055
Śabda brahma: spiritual sound.

22
00:01:40,056 --> 00:01:44,388
Guru Mahārāj said
one of the flaws of Islam is

23
00:01:44,696 --> 00:01:52,811
they can understand the sound divine,
but not the form divine.

24
00:01:53,027 --> 00:01:56,218
Name of God is …
that’s sound, divine sound,

25
00:01:56,218 --> 00:01:59,933
but why not divine form?

26
00:02:01,057 --> 00:02:06,156
You can rightfully say,
decry, or,

27
00:02:06,524 --> 00:02:09,404
what’s the word? Um …

28
00:02:10,219 --> 00:02:11,547
Another word …

29
00:02:11,547 --> 00:02:15,496
Your own part, 
“I’m not qualified.”

30
00:02:15,496 --> 00:02:17,245
That is all okay,

31
00:02:17,245 --> 00:02:21,302
but don’t say
“He’s unqualified.”

32
00:02:25,242 --> 00:02:29,225
Never say that: 
“He’s unqualified.”

33
00:02:29,225 --> 00:02:32,308
We’re unqualified, correct.

34
00:02:32,308 --> 00:02:35,287
He’s never unqualified.

35
00:02:36,950 --> 00:02:42,541
Nirguṇa doesn’t mean 
He’s unqualified.

36
00:02:43,281 --> 00:02:47,805
So, apāṇi-pādo javano-grahītāḥ
[Su: 3.19],

37
00:02:48,144 --> 00:02:54,442
He has no hands or legs
but He can receive offerings,

38
00:02:56,586 --> 00:03:02,337
and follow—you know—
be Sākṣi Gopāl. How?

39
00:03:02,337 --> 00:03:06,576
It’s divine form—divya-rūpām.

